<Action id="56984" issue="37649" author="denyeart" type="comment" created="2019-02-13 16:26:38.0" updateauthor="denyeart" updated="2019-02-13 16:26:38.0"> <body><! CDATA The client only submits one write-set (it chooses from one of the N peer responses), and then attaches the N endorsement signatures that it received from peers.  If any of the signatures do not match the write-set (actually the whole proposal response), you receive the error "The signature is invalid".  At validation time, the peer cannot distinguish whether the endorsing peer returned a different proposal response than the one that was ultimately submitted with the tran, or if it returned the same proposal response but somehow provided a bad signature for it.  All the validating peer knows is that the signature does not match the proposal response that was ultimately submitted.  That being said, I agree the message "The signature is invalid" could be improved to indicate that the signature does not match the proposal response, rather than being invalid for some other reason.  I was actually more confused by the message "identity 1 does not satisfy principal: the identity is a member of a different MSP (expected *************MSP, got *******MSP)".  I think both messages should be clarified with additional context.  ></body> </Action>
