<Action id="56987" issue="37649" author="jlcs" type="comment" created="2019-02-13 16:34:17.0" updateauthor="jlcs" updated="2019-02-13 16:34:17.0"> <body><! CDATA Thank you for the explanation. It makes so much sense now. Indeed, the tx from the orderer only needs to include once the read/write set.  The "expected *************MSP, got *******MSP" message is altered because the MSP names relate to internal information. You could read it as "expected MSP1, got MSP2". It is expected, as during the validation the peer compares the endorsing signature MSP to the endorsing policy MSP.  ></body> </Action>
